Articles.Content:
i recently decieded to clean up my ksp install of mods that i was not using (or at least thought i was not using). So I delete this and that, load ksp, and find that I can not use my latest launcher cause I deleted the parts for it.

Here is the problem....I dont know the name of the mod, have any pic's of the mod. All I can say is that its 0.23 compatible and it was from Japan.

Thanks for any help in pointing me towards it.

Uthgood
Does KSP output log mention the part name?
If you will post your launcher .craft here, we might be able to find the part that is probably causing it. Will you, please?

the only part that I dont recognize off hand is the following

part = HIIB.FS_4293431666

I know that there were two versions in the pack I downloaded and A and B

hope this helps

I looked over the name of the part, and it went really fast.

name of part is HIIB

FS is an abbreviation for mod.

Now think of mods you had with abbreviation FS.

Firespitter is first that comes to my mind, but checking through the Firespitter list of files I have not found any sign of HIIB part.

FScience also probable, but it does not contain parts I suppose.

So now it is up to you to think about how that mod might be called.

Or maybe someone might suggest what is this "HIIB"

HIIB maybe this? http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/51181-WIP-World-Space

Sure sounds like it... there's an H-IIA and and H-IIB *and* the H-II is a Japanese booster IRL.

0thats it. I had ended up with multiple saturn parts and had deleted the parts that I though were the ones that I didnt need (since i didnt think i needed two identical looking set of parts)

but yes, its the japanese booster that I was after.

thanks for all the help everyone.
